---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';

const metrics = [
  { label: 'Platform fee', value: '$0', note: 'was $400/yr' },
  { label: 'Google speed', value: '98', note: 'mobile score' },
  { label: 'Page weight', value: '193 KB', note: 'mobile home' },
  { label: 'Search setup', value: 'Live', note: 'sitemap + Console' },
];
---

<Base
  title="Case study: Rusty the Raccoon — Gian Trotta"
  description="How a children's book author escaped a $400/yr Wix bill, got a fast site Google can actually read, and kept every activity download working."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 pb-12 pt-16">
    <p class="font-utility text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-flare">Website Rescue · Case study</p>
    <h1 class="mt-4 font-display text-4xl font-bold leading-tight tracking-tight sm:text-5xl">
      Rusty the Raccoon
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-4 max-w-2xl text-lg text-mist">
      A children's book author was paying $400 a year for a site that told Google its name was
      "My Site." We rebuilt it in a day — same content, zero platform fee, and pages that load before
      you finish blinking.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-6">
      <a
        href="https://www.rustytheraccoon.com/"
        class="font-semibold text-steel underline"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noreferrer noopener"
      >
        See the live site →
      </a>
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Proof strip -->
  <section class="border-y border-line bg-white">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-10">
      <p class="font-utility text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-mist">At a glance</p>
      <dl class="mt-6 grid gap-px border border-line bg-line sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4">
        {
          metrics.map(({ label, value, note }) => (
            <div class="bg-white p-5">
              <dt class="font-utility text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-mist">{label}</dt>
              <dd class="mt-2 font-utility text-2xl font-bold text-steel">{value}</dd>
              <dd class="mt-1 font-utility text-xs text-mist">{note}</dd>
            </div>
          ))
        }
      </dl>
      <p class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-sm text-mist">
        Speed scores measured 2026-07-17 on the live site. No before scores exist — the Wix site was
        gone before we could run a comparison.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Problem -->
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-16">
    <p class="font-utility text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-flare">The problem</p>
    <h2 class="mt-3 font-display text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">Paying rent on a site Google ignored</h2>
    <div class="mt-6 max-w-3xl space-y-4 text-lg leading-relaxed text-mist">
      <p>
        Michelle Trotta wrote and published <em>Rusty the Raccoon is Scared of the Dark</em>, a
        picture book for kids who are nervous about the dark. Her site had seven pages — book info,
        author bio, free activity downloads, resource links, and videos. Nothing fancy. Just the
        kind of site a small publisher needs.
      </p>
      <p>
        The catch: it lived on Wix, and the annual bill was <strong class="text-ink">$400</strong>.
        The renewal was due August 3, 2026. Cancel the plan and the whole site disappears August 22.
      </p>
      <p>
        Worse, nobody had ever set up the basics for search. Every page title on the old site said
        <strong class="text-ink">"My Site."</strong> Not the book name. Not the author. Just "My Site,"
        on every single page. Google had almost nothing useful to work with.
      </p>
      <p>
        Michelle didn't want to change her content — she wanted the same words, the same downloads,
        the same look and feel. She just wanted to stop paying platform rent for a site that wasn't
        pulling its weight.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What we did -->
  <section class="border-t border-line bg-white">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-16">
      <p class="font-utility text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-flare">What we did</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-display text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">Rescue the content, then rebuild</h2>
      <div class="mt-8 grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-2">
        <article class="border border-line bg-porcelain p-6">
          <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold">1. Archive everything first</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-mist">
            Before touching the builder or the DNS, we downloaded every page, all 24 images, and
            all 11 activity PDFs. Once the content was safe on disk, the Wix deadline stopped being
            a hostage situation.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="border border-line bg-porcelain p-6">
          <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold">2. Rebuild by hand</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-mist">
            Seven pages rebuilt as a lightweight static site — no monthly platform, no bloated page
            builder. Same copy, cleaner URLs, and real page titles that describe what's actually on
            the page.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="border border-line bg-porcelain p-6">
          <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold">3. Make Google understand the book</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-mist">
            Unique titles and descriptions on every page. A sitemap. Structured data so search engines
            know this is a book by a real author with an Amazon link. Google Search Console registered
            and the sitemap submitted — all on launch day.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="border border-line bg-porcelain p-6">
          <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold">4. Keep the old links working</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-mist">
            Old Wix URLs still floating around on bookmarks and search results? Redirected. The
            activity PDFs people had linked to on the old file server? They still download. Michelle
            reviewed the preview and signed off before we touched the domain.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Results -->
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-16">
    <p class="font-utility text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-flare">Results</p>
    <h2 class="mt-3 font-display text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">The numbers</h2>

    <div class="mt-10 grid items-start gap-10 lg:grid-cols-12">
      <div class="lg:col-span-7">
        <div class="space-y-8">
          <article>
            <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold">$400/year → $0 hosting</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-mist">
              The Wix site plan was cancelled before the August renewal. Hosting is free. The only
              recurring cost left is domain registration through Wix until the contract ends in 2027.
            </p>
          </article>
          <article>
            <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold">"My Site" → real page titles</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-mist">
              The home page now opens with <em>Rusty the Raccoon is Scared of the Dark</em> — the
              actual book name. Every page has its own title and description. That's table stakes,
              but the old site never had it.
            </p>
          </article>
          <article>
            <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold">Sub-second loads, tiny pages</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-mist">
              On a phone, the home page weighs about 193 KB and scores 98/100 on Google's speed test.
              On desktop: 100/100, with the main content visible in under a third of a second. The
              server responds in about 30 milliseconds.
            </p>
          </article>
          <article>
            <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold">Registered with Google</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-mist">
              Search Console verified on launch day. Sitemap submitted. The site is set up to be
              crawled and indexed — a step the old Wix site never took.
            </p>
          </article>
        </div>

        <blockquote class="mt-10 border-l-4 border-flare pl-6">
          <p class="text-lg italic text-ink">
            Michelle reviewed the preview before we flipped the domain. Her verdict: she loves it.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>

      <!-- Receipt-style scoreboard -->
      <aside
        class="receipt-wrap lg:col-span-5 lg:rotate-1 motion-reduce:rotate-0"
        aria-label="Measured results from the live site"
      >
        <div class="receipt-paper px-7 py-9 font-utility">
          <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-mist">Site checkup · rustytheraccoon.com</p>
          <p class="mt-1 text-xs text-mist">Measured 2026-07-17</p>
          <dl class="mt-5 space-y-3 text-sm">
            <div class="flex justify-between gap-4 border-b border-dotted border-line pb-3">
              <dt>Mobile speed score</dt>
              <dd class="font-bold text-steel">98 / 100</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between gap-4 border-b border-dotted border-line pb-3">
              <dt>Desktop speed score</dt>
              <dd class="font-bold text-steel">100 / 100</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between gap-4 border-b border-dotted border-line pb-3">
              <dt>Mobile page weight</dt>
              <dd class="font-bold text-steel">193 KB</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between gap-4 border-b border-dotted border-line pb-3">
              <dt>Server response</dt>
              <dd class="font-bold text-steel">30 ms</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between gap-4 border-b border-dotted border-line pb-3">
              <dt>Accessibility</dt>
              <dd class="font-bold text-steel">100 / 100</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between gap-4">
              <dt>Monthly platform fee</dt>
              <dd class="font-bold text-flare">$0</dd>
            </div>
          </dl>
          <p class="mt-6 border-t border-dashed border-line pt-4 text-xs leading-relaxed text-mist">
            Before scores unavailable — the Wix site was removed before we could benchmark it. Cost
            savings and search setup are documented from the migration itself.
          </p>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Timeline note -->
  <section class="border-t border-line bg-white">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-12">
      <p class="font-utility text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-mist">Timeline</p>
      <p class="mt-3 max-w-3xl text-mist">
        The whole project — scrape, rebuild, design review, search setup, DNS cutover, and Wix
        cancellation — happened in one day: July 12, 2026. Michelle had a preview to approve before
        anything went live on her domain.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-16">
    <div class="border-2 border-dashed border-ink bg-white p-8 sm:p-10">
      <p class="font-utility text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-flare">Sound familiar?</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-display text-2xl font-bold sm:text-3xl">
        Paying monthly for a slow site that Google barely knows exists?
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-4 max-w-2xl text-mist">
        Start with a free 15-minute call or a fixed-price Site Checkup. You'll leave knowing what
        your site needs — whether or not we work together.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
        <a
          href="/contact/"
          class="rounded-md bg-flare-deep px-6 py-3 font-semibold text-porcelain hover:bg-flare"
        >
          Book a free call
        </a>
        <a
          href="/services/"
          class="rounded-md border border-ink px-6 py-3 font-semibold hover:bg-ink hover:text-porcelain"
        >
          See services
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
